<item>
            <title>[LU-3133] lfsck: should remove objects from OST nodes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3133</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Wen I do backport of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2663&quot; title=&quot;lfsck: e2fsck [QUOTA WARNING] Usage inconsistent&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2663&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2663&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to b1_8, lfsck test log shows&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;removing objects from /dev/lvm-OSS/P1 on ost1: 11 12
mount: mount point /mnt/ost1 does not exist
lfsck : @@@@@@ FAIL: removing objects failed 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To fix it, we should do remove_objects on OST nodes. I will push a patch later.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
